Home Newsroom News Releases Dana-Farber Cancer Institute names David Feinberg as VP, chief marketing officer



            Dana-Farber Cancer Institute names David Feinberg as VP, chief marketing officer
















April 11, 2017
Tags: Appointments


Previously led marketing for NewYork-Presbyterian HospitalDana-Farber Cancer Institute has named David A. Feinberg to the newly-created position of vice president and chief marketing officer (CMO). Feinberg previously served as vice president and chief marketing officer for New York-Presbyterian Hospital and Healthcare Network in New York City.“David is a proven leader who has led the development of some of healthcare’s best and most successful marketing campaigns,” said Laurie Glimcher, MD, president and CEO of Dana-Farber. “He understands healthcare deeply, and he is committed to our mission of improving the lives of people with cancer everywhere.”Feinberg joined New York-Presbyterian Hospital in 1997 as their first vice president of marketing, where he established a robust program to brand and market the hospital, which was created from the merger of The New York Hospital and The Presbyterian Hospital. As CMO, Feinberg was responsible for the development and implementation of marketing, advertising, physician referral, internet, and visitor information strategies. He is known for leading development of NewYork-Presbyterian’s “Amazing Things are Happening Here” campaign, widely recognized as one of the best of its kind.At Dana-Farber, Feinberg will be responsible for the strategic direction and day-to-day operations of consumer, digital and physician outreach programs to build the Institute’s brand visibility and clinical volume.“It is an honor to join the Dana-Farber family and work alongside some of the most accomplished physicians, researchers, and administrators anywhere,” Feinberg said. “Dana-Farber is a stellar organization, and I’m eager to help bring its message of quality care and research to an ever-wider range of people.”“I have known David and his work for years and am thrilled that he will be joining us,” said Steven Singer, senior vice president for communications at Dana-Farber. “David’s creativity, energy, and depth of experience will be a great asset to the entire Dana-Farber community.”Before joining New York Presbyterian, Feinberg led the health care practice of The Seiden Group, an advertising and marketing firm based in New York City. He began his career in the pharmaceutical and consumer industries, working at Procter & Gamble, Clairol and Ciba-Geigy (now Novartis). Feinberg graduated from the Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania with a Bachelor of Science degree in economics, and from Northwestern University’s Kellogg School of Management with a Master’s Degree in management and marketing.
















7/24/2017 1:26:27 AM










