Sloan Rules: Alfred P. Sloan and the Triumph of General Motors

by David Farber, D. Farber, David R. FarberDavid Farber




 


Alfred P. Sloan Jr. became the president of General Motors in 1923 and stepped down as its CEO in 1946. During this time, he led GM past the Ford Motor Company and on to international business triumph by virtue of his brilliant managerial practices and his insights into the new consumer economy he and GM helped to produce. Bill Gates has said that Sloan's 1964

